import Header from './Components/Header'
import MainPage from './Components/Mainpage'
export default function App(){
    return(
        <>
        <Header />
        <MainPage
            imag="./images/Mount_Fuji.webp"
            country="japan"
            name="Mount Fuji"
            location='https://www.google.com/maps/@35.3625,138.7322,15z/data=!4m5!3m4!'
            date="12 Jan,2021 - 24 Jan,2021"
            detail="Mount Fuji, also known as Fuji-san, is the highest and most celebrated mountain in Japan, standing at 3,776 meters. It is arguably the most perfect volcano cone in existence, with a symmetrical shape that has inspired artists, poets, and pilgrims for centuries."
        />
        <MainPage
            src="./images/great_wall_of_china.webp"
            country="China"
            name="Great Wall of China"
            location="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Great+Wall+of+China/@40.4319077,116.5703749,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x35f121d7687f2ccf:0xd040259b950522df!8m2!3d40.4319077!4d116.5703749!16zL20vMGQyZHEw?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI0MTIxMS4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D"
            date="13 Feb,2021 - 19 Feb,2021"
            detail="The Great Wall of China is an ancient series of fortifications built across the northern borders of China to protect the country from invasions by nomadic tribes. Stretching over 13,000 miles (21,000 km), it is one of the longest structures ever built."
        />
        <MainPage
            src="./images/statue-of-liberty.webp"
            country="America"
            name="Statue of Liberty"
            location="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Statue+of+Liberty/@40.6916124,-74.044429,16.75z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x89c25090129c363d:0x40c6a5770d25022b!8m2!3d40.6892494!4d-74.0445004!16zL20vMDcycDg?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI0MTIxMS4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D"
            date="01 April,2021 - 27 April,2021"
            detail="The Statue of Liberty, officially titled “Liberty Enlightening the World,” is a colossal neoclassical sculpture located on Liberty Island in New York Harbor. Designed by French sculptor Frédéric-Auguste Bartholdi and built by Gustave Eiffel, the statue was a gift from the people of France to the people of the United States, dedicated on October 28, 1886."
        />
        <MainPage
            src="./images/taj_mahal.webp"
            country="India"
            name="Taj Mahal"
            location='https://www.google.com/maps/place/Taj+Mahal/@27.1751447,78.0372713,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m14!1m7!3m6!1s0x39747121d702ff6d:0xdd2ae4803f767dde!2sTaj+Mahal!8m2!3d27.1751448!4d78.0421422!16zL20vMGw4Y2I!3m5!1s0x39747121d702ff6d:0xdd2ae4803f767dde!8m2!3d27.1751448!4d78.0421422!16zL20vMGw4Y2I?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI0MTIxMS4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D'
            date="01 June,2021 - 28 June,2021"
            detail="The Taj Mahal is a stunning white marble mausoleum complex located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. Built between 1632 and 1653, it was commissioned by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan as a tribute to his beloved wife, Mumtaz Mahal, who died in childbirth in 1631."
        />
        </>
    )
}
